  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-11-16",
    "date": "2023-08-15T16:14:18Z",
    "text": "Supporting Made in America Renewable and Traditional Energy Act or the SMART Energy Act\n\nThis bill directs the Department of the Interior to (1) conduct certain sales of leases of onshore and offshore federal land for the development of oil and gas; (2) establish priority areas for geothermal, solar, and wind energy projects on federal lands; and (3) review and make proposals for leasing federal offshore land for wind energy projects in the Atlantic and Pacific Regions of the outer Continental Shelf. The bill also limits delays on federal oil and gas leases."
